########ENGLISH TRANSLATION########
Post-doc position of a duration of 15-18 months

KNOWLEDGE EXTRACTION OUT OF TEXTUAL DATA AND CONCURRENT TIME SERIES

Start date: As soon as possible

Keywords: text mining, controlled natural languages, time series, =
anomaly detection

GENERAL CONTEXT:
Concurrence of textual data and of time series is a branch of text =
mining that emerged twenty years ago in the frame of the stock market =
where the following question has been asked: =E2=80=9Ccan we predict the =
evolution of the market out of text mining of the specialized press?=E2=80=
=9D.

This project aims to build similar methods in a different context, the =
one of improvement of energy performance and monitoring. The textual =
corpus we are going to use is the one of daily reports of a group of =
technicians supervising 24/25 the boilers of an industrial complex. The =
time series of our corpus are those of energy performance of the =
boilers, obtained by a multitude of sensors.

The technicians' reports are semi-structured documents written in a =
weakly controlled natural language. Special care will be given to =
detection of anomalies: these will be detected out of the textual corpus =
(out of structured parts of reports but also out of fragments in =
uncontrolled natural language) in correlation with unusual values in the =
time series.

OBJECTIVES:
We will first perform an unsupervised classification of times series' =
states, correlated with information extracted from the controlled =
natural language utterances, in order to obtain normality/anormality =
levels.

Then, after agreement with the data provider, we will focus on specific =
classes and will establish a predictive model based, concurrently, on =
the textual data and on the data originating from sensors.

Among the promising research tracks we expect a general method for =
correlating controlled natural language and time series as well as a =
possible retro-action: the optimization of the controlled language based =
on the predictive model. Switching to a strongly controlled language =
(with morphosyntactic and semantic validation based on an ad hoc =
ontology) would consolidate energetic optimization and anomaly =
prediction.

PARTNERS AND ACTORS:
The Learn-IA project gathers three actors: two companies from Rennes =
(Energiency and Script&Go) and a Grande =C3=89cole d'Ing=C3=A9nieurs =
(IMT Atlantique). It is funded by the European regional development fund =
(FEDER) and the R=C3=A9gion Bretagne-Atlantique. It has been labeled by =
the P=C3=B4le Images & R=C3=A9seaux and the P=C3=B4le Mer.

REFERENCES:
=E2=80=A2  Victor Lavrenko, Matt Schmill, Dawn Lawrie, Paul Ogilvie, =
David Jensen & James Allan, =E2=80=9CMining of concurrent text and time =
series,=E2=80=9D Proceedings of the 6th ACM SIGKDD, 2000
=E2=80=A2  Tao Yang & Dongwon Lee, =E2=80=9CT3: On Mapping Text To Times =
Series,=E2=80=9D The Alberto Mendelzon International Workshop on =
Foundations of Data Management (AMW), Arequipa, Peru, May 2009
=E2=80=A2  Sadi Ever Sekar, Cihan Mert, Khald Al-Naami & Nuro =C3=96zalp, =
=E2=80=9CTime Series Analysis on Stock Market for Text Mining =
Correlation of Economy News,=E2=80=9D International Journal of Social =
Sciences and Humanity Studies 6/1 (2014).
=E2=80=A2  Zeev Volkovich & Renata Avros, =E2=80=9CText Classification =
Using a Novel Times Series based Methodology,=E2=80=9D Procedia Computer =
Science 96 (2016) 53-62.
=E2=80=A2  David Obst, Badih Ghattas, Sandra Claudel, Jairo Cugliari, =
Yannig Goude & Georges Oppenheim, =E2=80=9CTextual Data for Time Series =
Forecasting,=E2=80=9D arXiv:1910.12618 (2019).

PREREQUISITES: a PhD either in natural language processing or in =
modeling of time series (with motivation in acquiring competencies in =
the area of natural language processing).

LOCATION: IMT Atlantique, Brest. (Laboratory Lab-STICC UMR CNRS 6285, =
DECIDE team)

START OF CONTRACT: ASAP

DURACTION OF CONTRACT: between 1( and 18 months

SALARY: approx. 2300=E2=82=AC per month (before taxes)

APPLICATION PROCESS: please send, in a single PDF file, your CV, =
motivation letter, publication list, the names of 2-3 referees or 2-3 =
recommandation letters. The file should be sent before November A5th, =
2020, midnight CET to:

