capteurs.</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;"><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;">Parmi les pistes de recherche prometteuses on peut =
envisager une m=C3=A9thode g=C3=A9n=C3=A9rale pour corr=C3=A9ler langage =
contr=C3=B4l=C3=A9 et s=C3=A9ries temporelles ainsi qu'une r=C3=A9tro-acti=
on : l'optimisation du langage contr=C3=B4l=C3=A9 vis-=C3=A0-vis du =
mod=C3=A8le pr=C3=A9dictif. Le passage =C3=A0 un langage fortement =
contr=C3=B4l=C3=A9 (avec validation morphosyntaxique et s=C3=A9mantique =
bas=C3=A9e sur une ontologie ad hoc) permettrait alors de consolider =
l'optimisation =C3=A9nerg=C3=A9tique et la pr=C3=A9diction =
d'anomalies.</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;"><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family:=
 HelveticaNeue;">PARTENAIRES ET ACTEURS :</div><div class=3D"" =
style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;">Le projet LEARN-IA r=C3=A9unit =
trois acteurs : deux entreprises rennaises (Energiency et Script&amp;Go) =
et une grande =C3=A9cole d'ing=C3=A9nieurs (IMT Atlantique), il est =
financ=C3=A9 par le Fonds europ=C3=A9en de d=C3=A9veloppement r=C3=A9giona=
l (FEDER) et la R=C3=A9gion Bretagne-Atlantique. Il a =C3=A9t=C3=A9 =
labellis=C3=A9 par le P=C3=B4le Images &amp; R=C3=A9seaux et le P=C3=B4le =
Mer.</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;"><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;">R=C3=89F=C3=89RENCES :</div><div class=3D"" =
style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;">=E2=80=A2 &nbsp;Victor Lavrenko, =
Matt Schmill, Dawn Lawrie, Paul Ogilvie, David Jensen &amp; James Allan, =
=E2=80=9CMining of concurrent text and time series,=E2=80=9D Proceedings =
of the 6th ACM SIGKDD, 2000</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;">=E2=80=A2 &nbsp;Tao Yang &amp; Dongwon Lee, =E2=80=9CT3: =
On Mapping Text To Times Series,=E2=80=9D The Alberto Mendelzon =
International Workshop on Foundations of Data Management (AMW), =
Arequipa, Peru, May 2009</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;">=E2=80=A2 &nbsp;Sadi Ever Sekar, Cihan Mert, Khald =
Al-Naami &amp; Nuro =C3=96zalp, =E2=80=9CTime Series Analysis on Stock =
Market for Text Mining Correlation of Economy News,=E2=80=9D =
International Journal of Social Sciences and Humanity Studies 6/1 =
(2014).</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;">=E2=80=A2=
 &nbsp;Zeev Volkovich &amp; Renata Avros, =E2=80=9CText Classification =
Using a Novel Times Series based Methodology,=E2=80=9D Procedia Computer =
Science 96 (2016) 53-62.</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;">=E2=80=A2 &nbsp;David Obst, Badih Ghattas, Sandra =
Claudel, Jairo Cugliari, Yannig Goude &amp; Georges Oppenheim, =
=E2=80=9CTextual Data for Time Series Forecasting,=E2=80=9D =
arXiv:1910.12618 (2019).</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;"><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family:=
 HelveticaNeue;">PR=C3=89REQUIS : th=C3=A8se de doctorat en traitement =
automatique du langage ou en mod=C3=A9lisation de s=C3=A9ries =
temporelles (avec motivation pour approfondir le domaine du traitement =
automatique de la langue).</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;"><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family:=
 HelveticaNeue;">LIEU : IMT Atlantique, Brest. (Laboratoire Lab-STICC =
UMR CNRS 6285, =C3=A9quipe DECIDE)</div><div class=3D"" =
style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;"><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D""=
 style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;">D=C3=89BUT DE CONTRAT : D=C3=A8s =
que possible</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;"><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family:=
 HelveticaNeue;">DUR=C3=89E DU CONTRAT : entre 15 et 18 mois</div><div =
class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;"><br class=3D""></div><div=
 class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;">R=C3=89MUN=C3=89RATION =
: environ 2300=E2=82=AC net/mois (avant pr=C3=A9l=C3=A8vement imp=C3=B4t =
=C3=A0 la source)</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;"><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family:=
 HelveticaNeue;">MODALIT=C3=89 DE CANDIDATURE : Le dossier de =
candidature doit comprendre, en un seul PDF, votre CV, lettre de =
motivation, liste de publications, les noms de 2-3 r=C3=A9f=C3=A9rents =
=C3=A0 contacter ou =C3=A9ventuellement des lettres de recommandation. =
Le dossier doit =C3=AAtre adress=C3=A9 avant le 15 novembre 2020 minuit =
=C3=A0:</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;"><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;">- =
&nbsp;Yannis Haralambous :&nbsp;<a =
href=3D"mailto:yannis.haralambous@imt-atlantique.fr" =
class=3D"">yannis.haralambous@imt-atlantique.fr</a></div><div class=3D"" =
style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;">- &nbsp;Philippe Lenca :&nbsp;<a =
href=3D"mailto:philippe.lenca@imt-atlantique.fr" =
class=3D"">philippe.lenca@imt-atlantique.fr</a></div><div class=3D"" =
style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;">- &nbsp;Lina Fahed :&nbsp;<a =
href=3D"mailto:lina.fahed@imt-atlantique.fr" =
class=3D"">lina.fahed@imt-atlantique.fr</a></div><div class=3D"" =
style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;"><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D""=
 style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;">########ENGLISH =
TRANSLATION########</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;">Post-doc position of a duration of 15-18 =
months</div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: HelveticaNeue;"><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;"><b class=3D"">KNOWLEDGE EXTRACTION OUT OF TEXTUAL DATA =
AND CONCURRENT TIME SERIES</b></div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family: =
HelveticaNeue;"><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"" style=3D"font-family:=
 HelveticaNeue;"><div class=3D"">Start date: As soon as =
possible</div><div class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div =
class=3D"">Keywords: text mining, controlled natural languages, time =
series, anomaly detection</div><div class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div =
class=3D"">GENERAL CONTEXT:</div><div class=3D"">Concurrence of textual =
data and of time series is a branch of text mining that emerged twenty =
years ago in the frame of the stock market where the following question =
has been asked: =E2=80=9Ccan we predict the evolution of the market out =
of text mining of the specialized press?=E2=80=9D.</div><div =
class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">This project aims to =
build similar methods in a different context, the one of improvement of =
energy performance and monitoring. The textual corpus we are going to =
use is the one of daily reports of a group of technicians supervising =
24/25 the boilers of an industrial complex. The time series of our =
corpus are those of energy performance of the boilers, obtained by a =
multitude of sensors.</div><div class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div =
class=3D"">The technicians' reports are semi-structured documents =
written in a weakly controlled natural language. Special care will be =
given to detection of anomalies: these will be detected out of the =
textual corpus (out of structured parts of reports but also out of =
fragments in uncontrolled natural language) in correlation with unusual =
values in the time series.</div><div class=3D""><br class=3D""></div><div =
class=3D"">OBJECTIVES:</div><div class=3D"">We will first perform an =
unsupervised classification of times series' states, correlated with =
information extracted from the controlled natural language utterances, =
in order to obtain normality/anormality levels.</div><div class=3D""><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">Then, after agreement with the data =
provider, we will focus on specific classes and will establish a =
predictive model based, concurrently, on the textual data and on the =
data originating from sensors.</div><div class=3D""><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">Among the promising research tracks we =
expect a general method for correlating controlled natural language and =
time series as well as a possible retro-action: the optimization of the =
controlled language based on the predictive model. Switching to a =
strongly controlled language (with morphosyntactic and semantic =
validation based on an ad hoc ontology) would consolidate energetic =
optimization and anomaly prediction.</div><div class=3D""><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">PARTNERS AND ACTORS:</div><div =
class=3D"">The Learn-IA project gathers three actors: two companies from =
Rennes (Energiency and Script&amp;Go) and a Grande =C3=89cole =
d'Ing=C3=A9nieurs (IMT Atlantique). It is funded by the European =
regional development fund (FEDER) and the R=C3=A9gion =
Bretagne-Atlantique. It has been labeled by the P=C3=B4le Images &amp; =
R=C3=A9seaux and the P=C3=B4le Mer.</div><div class=3D""><br =
class=3D""></div><div class=3D"">REFERENCES:</div><div class=3D"">=E2=80=A2=
 &nbsp;Victor Lavrenko, Matt Schmill, Dawn Lawrie, Paul Ogilvie, David =
Jensen &amp; James Allan, =E2=80=9CMining of concurrent text and time =
series,=E2=80=9D Proceedings of the 6th ACM SIGKDD, 2000</div><div =
class=3D"">=E2=80=A2 &nbsp;Tao Yang &amp; Dongwon Lee, =E2=80=9CT3: On =
Mapping Text To Times Series,=E2=80=9D The Alberto Mendelzon =
International Workshop on Foundations of Data Management (AMW), =
Arequipa, Peru, May 2009</div><div class=3D"">=E2=80=A2 &nbsp;Sadi Ever =
Sekar, Cihan Mert, Khald Al-Naami &amp; Nuro =C3=96zalp, =E2=80=9CTime =
